sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as Human User<br/>(browser)
    participant App as Web App<br/>(Postman today)
    participant AZ as Salesforce<br/>Authorize Endpoint
    participant T as Salesforce<br/>Token Endpoint
    participant API as Salesforce<br/>REST API

    Note over App: Creates a random code_verifier,<br/>hashes it → code_challenge (PKCE)
    App->>AZ: GET /services/oauth2/authorize<br/>response_type=code, client_id,<br/>redirect_uri, code_challenge
    AZ->>U: Salesforce login page + consent screen
    U->>AZ: Username + password (+ MFA), click Allow
    AZ-->>App: Redirect to callback URL<br/>?code=AUTH_CODE (temporary!)
    App->>T: POST /services/oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code, code,<br/>client_id, client_secret, redirect_uri,<br/>code_verifier (PKCE proof)
    T-->>App: access_token + refresh_token
    App->>API: GET /services/data/...<br/>Authorization: Bearer &lt;access_token&gt;
    API-->>App: JSON — as THIS user, with THEIR permissions

    Note over App,T: Later, when the access token expires…
    App->>T: POST /services/oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=refresh_token + refresh_token
    T-->>App: fresh access_token — no new login needed
